      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LISTEN SWEETHEART (8) matured over the break with a tough on-pace Maiden win over 1400m at Canberra. Can go on with it now in this tougher race from the low draw. DAMASCUS CALLING (3) proven at the trip and has a distinct fitness edge over these fifth-up. Worked home fairly with a battling third over 1400m at Kembla Grange. Grant Buckley retains the ride and looks to get the right tempo. WALK LIKE A MAN (2) demolished his rivals two-back at Kembla over this trip, then tackled the 1800m with a fading last at Newcastle in BM64 class. Complete mystery last start and gets another chance in this easier contest. SIR TUA (4) shouldered the 59kg when he failed to close off with a below par seventh over 1600m at Canberra. Key jockey change with Tommy Berry engaged. Each way.",
